Generate a no-leap (365-day) daily date sequence

Source: R/calendar.R
generate_noleap_dates.Rd

Constructs a continuous sequence of dates starting from a given start date, using a no-leap calendar (i.e., February 29 removed). The function repeats a 365-day month-day template and increments the year every 365 days.

Usage

generate_noleap_dates(start_date, n_days)

Arguments

start_date

Date or character coercible to Date. The first date of the sequence. If the date is February 29, it is mapped to February 28 because the no-leap template does not include Feb 29.

n_days

Integer. Total number of dates to generate.

Value

A vector of class Date with length n_days, following a no-leap (365-day) calendar.

Examples

generate_noleap_dates("1980-01-01", 365)
